in your sweet-bean soup.

00:09:14.596 --> 00:09:15.430 position:50% align:center
Is that it?

00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:16.806 position:50% align:center
That's a good analogy!

00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:19.184 position:50% align:center
Mm. I dunno if that's
what it was like.

00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:21.936 position:50% align:center
[NAYUTA]
Hmm.

00:09:22.020 --> 00:09:24.689 position:50% align:center
I think I'd actually like
to give that a taste.

00:09:24.773 --> 00:09:27.192 position:50% align:center
[BARON'S OWNER]
You can. We serve it.

00:09:27.275 --> 00:09:28.318 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
What?

00:09:28.401 --> 00:09:29.652 position:50% align:center
You do?

00:09:29.736 --> 00:09:32.572 position:50% align:center
The secret menu's nuts!
What don't they have here?

00:09:32.655 --> 00:09:35.200 position:50% align:center
That flat-udon-and-
sweet-bean-paste Napolitan

00:09:35.283 --> 00:09:36.785 position:50% align:center
was truly horrifying.

00:09:36.868 --> 00:09:39.954 position:50% align:center
Though I have to admit it had
a depth of flavor all its own.

00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:41.873 position:50% align:center
[BARON'S OWNER]
Mm-hm.

00:09:42.957 --> 00:09:44.542 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Hey, come to think of it,

00:09:44.626 --> 00:09:47.170 position:50% align:center
didn't you two graduate
from Shoka-Yono High?

00:09:47.253 --> 00:09:48.004 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
Yeah.

00:09:48.088 --> 00:09:49.464 position:50% align:center
And in all your years there,

00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:52.217 position:50% align:center
you never once went on stage
for the culture festival?

00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:54.219 position:50% align:center
No, we never got the chance to.

00:09:54.302 --> 00:09:57.013 position:50% align:center
Heh. Unfortunately not.

00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:01.267 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU] Fubuki and I only
paired up three years ago.

00:10:01.351 --> 00:10:04.104 position:50% align:center
It was during our second
year of high school.

00:10:04.187 --> 00:10:05.730 position:50% align:center
It's our anti-smoking week!

00:10:05.814 --> 00:10:07.982 position:50% align:center
Rock 'n' roll!

00:10:08.066 --> 00:10:11.111 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU grunting]

00:10:12.195 --> 00:10:13.363 position:50% align:center
Rock 'n' roll.

00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:14.823 position:50% align:center
Shake it up, baby, now.

00:10:14.906 --> 00:10:17.409 position:50% align:center
[SCHOOLGIRLS giggling]

00:10:17.492 --> 00:10:19.744 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU] We used to just mess
around between classes

00:10:19.828 --> 00:10:21.579 position:50% align:center
with little gags and stuff,

00:10:21.663 --> 00:10:24.833 position:50% align:center
but all our classmates thought
we were really funny.

00:10:24.916 --> 00:10:29.004 position:50% align:center
So, we rolled with it and
teamed up. And then...

00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:30.755 position:50% align:center
Oh! Wait I remember now.

00:10:30.839 --> 00:10:32.007 position:50% align:center
Huh? What?

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.884 position:50% align:center
Now that I think about
it, that gag...

00:10:34.968 --> 00:10:37.512 position:50% align:center
"Please don't rush when
entering the train."

00:10:37.595 --> 00:10:41.141 position:50% align:center
Here they go. Pshh. Pshh.

00:10:41.224 --> 00:10:46.563 position:50% align:center
[spluttering]

00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:50.275 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Not to sound
like a broken record,

00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:52.902 position:50% align:center
but it always bombed
back then, too.

00:10:53.987 --> 00:10:56.781 position:50% align:center
Every time she did it,
there wasn't even a chuckle.

00:10:56.865 --> 00:10:59.159 position:50% align:center
I guess that is how
things kinda went.

00:10:59.242 --> 00:11:01.911 position:50% align:center
Aw, I could've done any bit,
why'd I do that one?

00:11:01.995 --> 00:11:04.080 position:50% align:center
I wonder if being back
at Shoka-Yono High

00:11:04.164 --> 00:11:07.167 position:50% align:center
just made my muscle memory
kick in or something.

00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:09.169 position:50% align:center
Hey, I think this story's
getting off-track.

00:11:09.252 --> 00:11:10.670 position:50% align:center
So, what happened next?

00:11:10.754 --> 00:11:13.298 position:50% align:center
You got caught up in the moment,
formed a duo, and then...

00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:16.051 position:50% align:center
Right. We weren't getting
caught up in things though.

00:11:16.134 --> 00:11:17.927 position:50% align:center
Just kinda giving in to it all.

00:11:18.011 --> 00:11:20.430 position:50% align:center
Then we got into the
High-School Comedy Contest.

00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:22.682 position:50% align:center
Only as far as the
preliminaries, though.

00:11:22.766 --> 00:11:24.684 position:50% align:center
We lost, but it's
because we got cut

00:11:24.768 --> 00:11:26.269 position:50% align:center
that we felt like there's
no way we could

00:11:26.353 --> 00:11:27.479 position:50% align:center
let things end with that.

00:11:27.562 --> 00:11:29.564 position:50% align:center
And if we had given up
on comedy back then,

00:11:29.647 --> 00:11:31.191 position:50% align:center
we wouldn't be here today!

00:11:31.274 --> 00:11:32.317 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
Mm.

00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:33.735 position:50% align:center
I do wonder, though.

00:11:33.818 --> 00:11:35.695 position:50% align:center
Maybe it would have been
better if we had given up.

00:11:35.779 --> 00:11:37.947 position:50% align:center
What? You really think
we should have?

00:11:38.031 --> 00:11:39.199 position:50% align:center
Just kidding!

00:11:39.282 --> 00:11:41.659 position:50% align:center
You really had me going.

00:11:43.787 --> 00:11:47.207 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU] Maybe we should just
join a talent agency already.

00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:49.042 position:50% align:center
Even if we did it
doesn't guarantee that

00:11:49.125 --> 00:11:50.960 position:50% align:center
we'll get work out of it.

00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.087 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:11:52.170 --> 00:11:54.130 position:50% align:center
Though, it sorta
seems like JK Cool

00:11:54.214 --> 00:11:56.216 position:50% align:center
is getting a steady
stream of gigs.

00:11:56.299 --> 00:11:58.259 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
That's good for them.

00:12:00.303 --> 00:12:01.596 position:50% align:center
[beeping]

00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:02.430 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Hm?

00:12:02.514 --> 00:12:03.515 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Look at the time!

00:12:03.598 --> 00:12:04.849 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
Got work?

00:12:04.933 --> 00:12:07.477 position:50% align:center
Yeah, Rin and I actually
have the late shift today.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:08.812 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Oh, you do?

00:12:08.895 --> 00:12:11.398 position:50% align:center
Mafuyu and I were supposed
to be on the early shift

00:12:11.481 --> 00:12:14.776 position:50% align:center
but we ended up taking the
day off at the last minute.

00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:17.237 position:50% align:center
[TOMITA]
Welcome!

00:12:17.320 --> 00:12:21.366 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] We must've left Tomita
and Hatsuna in a bind.

00:12:21.449 --> 00:12:22.992 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Well, see you tomorrow.

00:12:23.076 --> 00:12:26.037 position:50% align:center
See you later.
Good work today, everyone.

00:12:27.831 --> 00:12:29.207 position:50% align:center
I can't believe Rin and Na

00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:30.875 position:50% align:center
are going to college
while doing this.

00:12:30.959 --> 00:12:34.462 position:50% align:center
Good lord! It's clear we
have more time than they do!

00:12:34.546 --> 00:12:35.714 position:50% align:center
Goodness it's almost criminal!

00:12:35.797 --> 00:12:36.715 position:50% align:center
[CARLOS]
Dessert.

00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:38.258 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
Huh? We didn't order that.

00:12:38.341 --> 00:12:42.929 position:50% align:center
Sweet-bean soup on us.
Comes with xiaolongbao.

00:12:43.013 --> 00:12:44.723 position:50% align:center
Taste the sensation.

00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:46.641 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Cool beans!

00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:52.230 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER A] All students must
leave the school grounds by 5pm.

00:12:52.313 --> 00:12:54.232 position:50% align:center
There will be a prep
committee meeting...

00:12:54.315 --> 00:12:56.985 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU sighs] We managed to
get through the first day.

00:12:57.068 --> 00:12:58.319 position:50% align:center
Sure did.

00:12:58.403 --> 00:13:00.613 position:50% align:center
We owe Fuyu a lot for
helping us outta that jam.

00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:03.575 position:50% align:center
"A concert is a concert,
and comedy is comedy!"

00:13:03.658 --> 00:13:05.493 position:50% align:center
Don't forget she
complained just like that.

00:13:05.577 --> 00:13:07.162 position:50% align:center
We'll have to invite
them back next year

00:13:07.245 --> 00:13:08.496 position:50% align:center
for their real routine.

00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:11.332 position:50% align:center
Yeah. They'll all just
have to become superstars

00:13:11.416 --> 00:13:12.834 position:50% align:center
between now and then.

00:13:12.917 --> 00:13:14.961 position:50% align:center
If they're already really
popular, it'll make convincing

00:13:15.045 --> 00:13:16.504 position:50% align:center
the committee a
whole lot easier!

00:13:16.588 --> 00:13:17.714 position:50% align:center
[KANAE]
Mm. Yeah totally!

00:13:17.797 --> 00:13:18.631 position:50% align:center
[MS HIRANO]
Miss Kogarashi!

00:13:18.715 --> 00:13:19.507 position:50% align:center
--[MANATSU] Hm?
--[KANAE] Huh?

00:13:19.591 --> 00:13:20.925 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU]
Ms. Hirano.

00:13:21.009 --> 00:13:23.720 position:50% align:center
About the lead singer in that
all-girl airband today.

00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:25.722 position:50% align:center
If I'm not mistaken,
that was your sister,

00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:27.640 position:50% align:center
Mafuyu Kogarashi, wasn't it?

00:13:27.724 --> 00:13:31.144 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh? I had no idea
you knew my big sister.

00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:33.021 position:50% align:center
Well, I happened to be
her homeroom teacher

00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:35.899 position:50% align:center
when she used to go here for
both her second and third years.

00:13:35.982 --> 00:13:38.693 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU]
Oh! So that's how you know her!

00:13:38.777 --> 00:13:40.737 position:50% align:center
I know Miss Kitakaze, too.

00:13:40.820 --> 00:13:43.031 position:50% align:center
Those two are still
doing comedy together?

00:13:43.114 --> 00:13:44.741 position:50% align:center
Yeah, they sure are.

00:13:44.824 --> 00:13:46.493 position:50% align:center
They're kind of still
in training though,

00:13:46.576 --> 00:13:48.036 position:50% align:center
while they're
working part-time.

00:13:48.119 --> 00:13:50.413 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:13:50.497 --> 00:13:52.207 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU, KANAE]
Huh?

00:13:54.250 --> 00:13:56.378 position:50% align:center
That bit of hers...

00:13:59.506 --> 00:14:01.675 position:50% align:center
"Please don't rush when
entering the train."

00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:05.929 position:50% align:center
Here they go. Pshh.

00:14:06.012 --> 00:14:10.892 position:50% align:center
[spluttering]

00:14:11.893 --> 00:14:14.562 position:50% align:center
[exhales]

00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.649 position:50% align:center
Sorry. It's that bit she always
does of an impression

00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:21.903 position:50% align:center
of an anime character doing an
impression of another character.

00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:24.072 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:14:24.155 --> 00:14:27.200 position:50% align:center
She's been doing that routine
ever since her high school days!

00:14:27.283 --> 00:14:28.702 position:50% align:center
She's been doing it that long?

00:14:28.785 --> 00:14:30.328 position:50% align:center
What'll we do with her.

00:14:30.412 --> 00:14:33.915 position:50% align:center
And just like today,
it would never fail to bomb.

00:14:34.916 --> 00:14:38.461 position:50% align:center
I hadn't seen it in a while,
and I couldn't stop laughing.

00:14:38.545 --> 00:14:39.713 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:14:39.796 --> 00:14:43.258 position:50% align:center
Ms. Hirano, that bit of
hers isn't funny at all.

00:14:43.341 --> 00:14:44.592 position:50% align:center
[KANAE]
Mm-mm.

00:14:44.676 --> 00:14:47.387 position:50% align:center
Please don't feel like
you need to be polite!

00:14:47.470 --> 00:14:49.973 position:50% align:center
I did think to myself,
"Wow, she's still doing

00:14:50.056 --> 00:14:51.349 position:50% align:center
that oddball impression?"

00:14:51.433 --> 00:14:55.228 position:50% align:center
But for some strange reason,
it's really grown on me!

00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:56.730 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Huh...

00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:58.481 position:50% align:center
[MS HIRANO]
Well, it's like this:

00:14:58.565 --> 00:15:00.650 position:50% align:center
I've seen her do it
over and over again,

00:15:00.734 --> 00:15:03.403 position:50% align:center
and now after like
seeing it a million times

00:15:03.486 --> 00:15:04.988 position:50% align:center
it's starting to be funny to me!

00:15:05.071 --> 00:15:06.740 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:10.243 position:50% align:center
If my sister heard you say that,
she'd be so happy she'd cry!

00:15:10.326 --> 00:15:12.871 position:50% align:center
Even at home, that
impression always bombs.

00:15:12.954 --> 00:15:16.041 position:50% align:center
Oh, right. There's something
I wanted to tell those two.

00:15:16.124 --> 00:15:16.958 position:50% align:center
--[KANAE] Uh?
--[MANATSU] Mm?

00:15:17.042 --> 00:15:19.627 position:50% align:center
To Fubuki and Sis?

00:15:19.711 --> 00:15:21.629 position:50% align:center
"Keep on doing
your best, girls."

00:15:21.713 --> 00:15:23.757 position:50% align:center
Would you mind
passing that along?

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:28.011 position:50% align:center
Ah. Of course!
I'll let them know.

00:15:28.094 --> 00:15:30.638 position:50% align:center
Well then, good luck with
day two of the festival!

00:15:30.722 --> 00:15:32.557 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU]
Thank you, Ms. Hirano!

00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:35.185 position:50% align:center
[MS HIRANO]
Careful getting home now!

00:15:35.268 --> 00:15:36.436 position:50% align:center
[BOTH laugh]

00:15:42.776 --> 00:15:45.028 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU] So, our hook is
the bottom half of a moai.

00:15:45.111 --> 00:15:46.738 position:50% align:center
Does that sound good?

00:15:46.821 --> 00:15:49.282 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Do we sit knees-up,
cross-legged, formally,

00:15:49.366 --> 00:15:50.658 position:50% align:center
or with legs to the side?

00:15:50.742 --> 00:15:52.660 position:50% align:center
I dunno. Why don't we
just sit however

00:15:52.744 --> 00:15:54.662 position:50% align:center
we want and see
how things turn out?

00:15:54.746 --> 00:15:56.790 position:50% align:center
But if we end up shifting
around during the bit,

00:15:56.873 --> 00:15:58.416 position:50% align:center
won't it ruin the tempo?

00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:01.503 position:50% align:center
I guess that's true.
It's like da-da-da-da-DA!

00:16:01.586 --> 00:16:04.047 position:50% align:center
That's the kind of pace we
should be shooting for.

00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:05.423 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Hmm...

00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:08.426 position:50% align:center
Well, why don't we just
try it and see how it goes.

00:16:08.510 --> 00:16:11.304 position:50% align:center
And then we'll know if
our feet cramp up or not.

00:16:11.388 --> 00:16:13.181 position:50% align:center
You sound like an old lady.

00:16:13.264 --> 00:16:16.351 position:50% align:center
Well, we're not going to
be teenagers for much longer.

00:16:16.434 --> 00:16:18.728 position:50% align:center
No one stays young forever.

00:16:20.397 --> 00:16:23.316 position:50% align:center
You're right. Can't deny that.

00:16:23.400 --> 00:16:25.694 position:50% align:center
What's wrong? Is something
bothering you?

00:16:25.777 --> 00:16:26.945 position:50% align:center
It's nothing.

00:16:27.028 --> 00:16:28.947 position:50% align:center
That chat with Rin and
Nayuta today about how

00:16:29.030 --> 00:16:30.907 position:50% align:center
we teamed up has
just been on my mind.

00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:32.701 position:50% align:center
It really got me thinking.

00:16:32.784 --> 00:16:34.869 position:50% align:center
Oh, you mean about how your
train-door gag is still

00:16:34.953 --> 00:16:35.704 position:50% align:center
falling flat with crowds?

00:16:35.787 --> 00:16:37.205 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
No not about that!

00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:38.707 position:50% align:center
Then what?

00:16:38.790 --> 00:16:40.709 position:50% align:center
The High-School comedy contest.

00:16:40.792 --> 00:16:42.627 position:50% align:center
After we got cut in
the preliminary round

00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:44.337 position:50% align:center
for the second year in a row.

00:16:51.052 --> 00:16:54.973 position:50% align:center
Looks like we're
eliminated. Again.

00:16:55.056 --> 00:16:56.016 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:16:58.810 --> 00:17:01.604 position:50% align:center
Mafuyu, what are you thinking?
Say something.

00:17:01.688 --> 00:17:03.314 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:17:05.942 --> 00:17:08.862 position:50% align:center
I just don't want things
to end this way.

00:17:08.945 --> 00:17:09.988 position:50% align:center
What do you think?

00:17:10.071 --> 00:17:12.407 position:50% align:center
I feel the same as you.

00:17:21.541 --> 00:17:23.626 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
Nothing's changed.

00:17:23.710 --> 00:17:25.378 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:17:25.462 --> 00:17:29.132 position:50% align:center
Which is why we aren't gonna
let things end this way.

00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:31.634 position:50% align:center
Of course not!

00:17:31.718 --> 00:17:34.888 position:50% align:center
So, on that note, let's talk
about that impression of yours.

00:17:34.971 --> 00:17:36.389 position:50% align:center
Are you still on that?

00:17:36.473 --> 00:17:39.100 position:50% align:center
I am! Ninety percent
of honing one's craft

00:17:39.184 --> 00:17:42.270 position:50% align:center
is about constructive criticism.
So, let's start!

00:17:42.354 --> 00:17:44.814 position:50% align:center
Ugh... Who said that?

00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:46.566 position:50% align:center
I just did!

00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:49.194 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU groans]

00:17:49.277 --> 00:17:52.072 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I was just thinking
something about that gag.

00:17:52.155 --> 00:17:55.075 position:50% align:center
Is it possible that it
might be too faithful?

00:17:55.158 --> 00:17:58.328 position:50% align:center
Hmm... What if you gave
it a little twist instead?

00:17:58.411 --> 00:18:02.082 position:50% align:center
Wait do you mean my Konata?
Oh no is it my Shin-chan?

00:18:02.165 --> 00:18:05.085 position:50% align:center
Neither of them! If you rework
that part of the routine,

00:18:05.168 --> 00:18:06.836 position:50% align:center
then it wouldn't be an
impression anymore!

00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:08.838 position:50% align:center
Change the train-door part!

00:18:08.922 --> 00:18:12.008 position:50% align:center
I dunno. If I did that,
the audience

00:18:12.092 --> 00:18:13.968 position:50% align:center
wouldn't be able to tell
what the joke's about.

00:18:14.052 --> 00:18:16.096 position:50% align:center
I suppose that's true.

00:18:16.179 --> 00:18:19.224 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU] Hmm, what other
part can I tweak.

00:18:19.307 --> 00:18:20.725 position:50% align:center
That is the question

00:18:20.809 --> 00:18:22.727 position:50% align:center
Hey, look. Isn't that
Fuyu and Fubuki?

00:18:22.811 --> 00:18:25.188 position:50% align:center
Oh, it sure is!

00:18:25.271 --> 00:18:28.191 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:18:30.694 --> 00:18:32.654 position:50% align:center
Natsu?

00:18:32.737 --> 00:18:34.739 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU]
She looks so focused.

00:18:34.823 --> 00:18:36.866 position:50% align:center
I have to say, this
might be the first time

00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:39.828 position:50% align:center
I've ever seen her serious side.

00:18:39.911 --> 00:18:43.748 position:50% align:center
[KANAE]
Hm. Huh?

00:18:43.832 --> 00:18:45.750 position:50% align:center
Guess that's true.

00:18:48.169 --> 00:18:50.255 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Well, what if you
change the sound of the train?

00:18:50.338 --> 00:18:52.007 position:50% align:center
You could make it
some other melody.

00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:54.509 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah! I think I see
where you're going.

00:18:54.592 --> 00:18:57.595 position:50% align:center
Like maybe something
you would never ever hear.

00:18:57.679 --> 00:18:59.097 position:50% align:center
That could really work.

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:02.600 position:50% align:center
I wonder if there's
one that'll do the trick.

00:19:02.684 --> 00:19:04.102 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU]
Hey, Sis!

00:19:04.185 --> 00:19:06.730 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU]
Oh, Manatsu! Kanae!

00:19:06.813 --> 00:19:08.857 position:50% align:center
What're you doing here?

00:19:08.940 --> 00:19:10.734 position:50% align:center
We were just on our way home.

00:19:10.817 --> 00:19:12.986 position:50% align:center
Thanks again for
all your help today.

00:19:13.069 --> 00:19:14.404 position:50% align:center
Don't mention it!

00:19:14.487 --> 00:19:17.115 position:50% align:center
Honestly, we ought to be
thanking you for inviting us.

00:19:17.198 --> 00:19:19.367 position:50% align:center
What she said! Thanks a ton!

00:19:19.451 --> 00:19:22.746 position:50% align:center
--Wha--?
--[laughing]

00:19:22.829 --> 00:19:25.874 position:50% align:center
Heh, oh, Kanae. You're
the best audience ever!

00:19:25.957 --> 00:19:27.876 position:50% align:center
She really is, isn't she?

00:19:27.959 --> 00:19:29.711 position:50% align:center
Hearing her laugh
really perks me up,

00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:32.714 position:50% align:center
especially on days like today
when I'm feeling blue.

00:19:32.797 --> 00:19:35.133 position:50% align:center
Thank you, Kanae!

00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:37.635 position:50% align:center
You should take a page
out of her book Manatsu.

00:19:37.719 --> 00:19:39.220 position:50% align:center
[MANATSU]
Oh, really.

00:19:39.304 --> 00:19:41.556 position:50% align:center
You know, there was something
really nice I was gonna share

00:19:41.639 --> 00:19:43.266 position:50% align:center
with you, but if you're
gonna talk like that,

00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:44.434 position:50% align:center
I'm not gonna say it.

00:19:44.517 --> 00:19:46.770 position:50% align:center
Well, wait, now I
wanna know what it is.

00:19:46.853 --> 00:19:49.981 position:50% align:center
Come on, quit acting all high
and mighty and just spill it.

00:19:50.065 --> 00:19:53.276 position:50% align:center
Sure. You remember
Ms. Hirano, don't you?

00:19:53.360 --> 00:19:54.778 position:50% align:center
Yeah, of course!

00:19:54.861 --> 00:19:56.863 position:50% align:center
How is she doing?

00:20:01.117 --> 00:20:02.285 position:50% align:center
[RIN]
Hey, Nayuta.

00:20:02.369 --> 00:20:04.537 position:50% align:center
Do you wanna come over
to my place after work?

00:20:04.621 --> 00:20:06.831 position:50% align:center
Huh? I guess I can.

00:20:06.915 --> 00:20:09.042 position:50% align:center
Did you want to
go over some skits?

00:20:09.125 --> 00:20:11.294 position:50% align:center
That's not why I'm asking.

00:20:11.378 --> 00:20:14.798 position:50% align:center
It's because my report's not
finished, and it's due tomorrow.

00:20:14.881 --> 00:20:16.257 position:50% align:center
Another one?

00:20:16.341 --> 00:20:18.802 position:50% align:center
You're hopeless, what are
we going to do with you.

00:20:18.885 --> 00:20:21.763 position:50% align:center
One deluxe set!
Dipping sauce only.

00:20:21.846 --> 00:20:23.473 position:50% align:center
Wait, what?

00:20:27.769 --> 00:20:31.314 position:50% align:center
That was nice.
Ms. Hirano said that, huh?

00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:33.566 position:50% align:center
She actually complimented us.

00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:36.319 position:50% align:center
Huh? Fubuki!

00:20:36.403 --> 00:20:37.570 position:50% align:center
Know what this means?

00:20:37.654 --> 00:20:39.155 position:50% align:center
I don't think so...

00:20:39.239 --> 00:20:41.616 position:50% align:center
It's like Ms. Hirano said: if
you see it over and over again,

00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:45.036 position:50% align:center
it'll eventually grow on you!

00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:46.788 position:50% align:center
Where are you going with this?

00:20:46.871 --> 00:20:48.665 position:50% align:center
I'm talking about
the train-door gag!

00:20:48.748 --> 00:20:51.918 position:50% align:center
If I just keep doing it nonstop
"Not again!" will turn into

00:20:52.002 --> 00:20:53.795 position:50% align:center
"It still doesn't
sound quite right."

00:20:53.878 --> 00:20:55.797 position:50% align:center
Till at last it becomes
"You know what?

00:20:55.880 --> 00:20:57.757 position:50% align:center
I'm actually sensing a
deeper meaning here!"

00:20:57.841 --> 00:20:59.551 position:50% align:center
So, it's the kind of shtick
that people learn

00:20:59.634 --> 00:21:01.678 position:50% align:center
to appreciate over time!

00:21:01.761 --> 00:21:03.430 position:50% align:center
How does that even work?

00:21:03.513 --> 00:21:05.765 position:50% align:center
It means if I keep hammering
away, it may never get

00:21:05.849 --> 00:21:08.435 position:50% align:center
huge laughs, but I bet
it'll get some chuckles!

00:21:08.518 --> 00:21:10.395 position:50% align:center
I think this could
really work, Fubuki!

00:21:10.478 --> 00:21:12.188 position:50% align:center
Let's go all in on this!

00:21:12.272 --> 00:21:14.607 position:50% align:center
So, what you're saying is that
you'll do that bit forever,

00:21:14.691 --> 00:21:16.192 position:50% align:center
even if it bombs?

00:21:16.276 --> 00:21:18.319 position:50% align:center
I have a feeling you're
going to get discouraged

00:21:18.403 --> 00:21:20.697 position:50% align:center
long before you get a chuckle.

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:21.573 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:21:21.656 --> 00:21:23.324 position:50% align:center
Think of this mental image:

00:21:23.408 --> 00:21:25.243 position:50% align:center
it'd be like spending
a freezing winter

00:21:25.326 --> 00:21:27.787 position:50% align:center
at the South Pole wearing
nothing but a T-shirt.

00:21:27.871 --> 00:21:28.955 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:29.039 --> 00:21:30.957 position:50% align:center
Do you want to freeze to death?

00:21:31.041 --> 00:21:36.046 position:50% align:center
Ahh! I've changed my mind!
That's sounds awful!

00:21:42.302 --> 00:21:44.346 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
A train door, huh?

00:21:44.429 --> 00:21:47.557 position:50% align:center
Mafuyu's not that great at
impressions in the first place,

00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:49.559 position:50% align:center
so that's a tough one.

00:21:49.642 --> 00:21:51.519 position:50% align:center
Hmm...

00:21:52.937 --> 00:21:55.607 position:50% align:center
"Please don't rush
when entering the train."

00:21:55.690 --> 00:21:58.651 position:50% align:center
Here they go. Pshh...

00:21:58.735 --> 00:22:00.362 position:50% align:center
Pshh, pshh.

00:22:00.445 --> 00:22:02.989 position:50% align:center
Do, do, do, do...

00:22:03.073 --> 00:22:08.370 position:50% align:center
Ohh, ohhh, ohhh...

00:22:09.204 --> 00:22:12.665 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI laughing]

00:22:17.879 --> 00:22:19.464 position:50% align:center
[TOMITA]
Hey, I heard the news!

00:22:19.547 --> 00:22:21.591 position:50% align:center
There was a big hit
and a huge miss

00:22:21.675 --> 00:22:23.259 position:50% align:center
at that festival yesterday, huh?

00:22:23.343 --> 00:22:25.970 position:50% align:center
Tomita. C'mon quit
talking about that.

00:22:26.054 --> 00:22:28.139 position:50% align:center
You know that she's
bummed out over it.

00:22:28.223 --> 00:22:31.726 position:50% align:center
Nu-uh! I think that bit
is great just the way it is.

00:22:31.810 --> 00:22:34.729 position:50% align:center
Not again. Is she back on that?

00:22:34.813 --> 00:22:38.733 position:50% align:center
Hey guys, have you ever
heard of a "way homer"?

00:22:38.817 --> 00:22:40.235 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:24:15.955 --> 00:24:17.457 position:50% align:center
[MAFUYU, FUBUKI]
What's next on Maesetsu?

00:24:17.540 --> 00:24:18.458 position:50% align:center
[RIN, NAYUTA]
"Thrills!"

00:24:18.541 --> 00:24:19.793 position:50% align:center
[TOMITA, HATSUNA]
Don't miss it!